              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "Because patients tend to like, respect, and trust physicians, they are willing to pay large amounts of money to maintain close relationships with them."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "Physicians limit the access of minority members to the resources needed to become a physician so they can retain for the dominant group the income, power, and prestige that accompany their occupation."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "The occupation of physician is more highly valued than that of bus driver and requires much more sacrifice in terms of education and training. Providing physicians with greater rewards ensures that some people will be willing to make these sacrifices."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "Due to high stress and responsibility, physicians have a shorter life span than do bus drivers and hence a much shorter period of time in which to earn money."
